### TERMS AND CONDITIONS

0. **Definitions**  
"This License" refers to version 3 of the GNU Affero General Public License.  
"The Program" refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this License. Each licensee is addressed as "you."  
To "modify" a work means to copy from or adapt all or part of the work in a fashion requiring copyright permission.  
A "covered work" means either the unmodified Program or a work based on the Program.  
To "convey" a work means any kind of propagation that enables other parties to make or receive copies.  
An interactive user interface displays "Appropriate Legal Notices" if it includes a convenient feature that displays a copyright notice and tells the user that the work has no warranty.

1. **Source Code**  
The "source code" means the preferred form of the work for making modifications. "Object code" refers to any non-source form of a work.

2. **Basic Permissions**  
All rights granted under this License are provided free of charge. You may modify and distribute the Program's source code or object code, provided that you follow the conditions outlined in this License.

3. **Conveying Copies**  
You may convey copies of the source code as long as you provide the license and disclaimers of warranty. You must also ensure that recipients can access the source code.

4. **Conveying Modified Source Versions**  
If you modify a covered work, you must make it available under this License to others. This includes sharing source code for any modified version that is distributed or made available over a network.

5. **Conveying Non-Source Forms**  
You may convey non-source forms (e.g., object code), provided that you either include the source code or a written offer to provide the source code.

6. **Additional Terms**  
You cannot impose further restrictions on the rights granted by this License. Any additional restrictions are null and void.

7. **Termination**  
If you violate the terms of this License, your rights under this License are terminated.

